The paper deals with capacity expressions and communication scenarios, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The examples of random access channels and wireless systems suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the Multimedia (cs.MM) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The discussion of genie-aided outerbounds and capacity bounds suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) and Signal Processing (cs.SI) sub-categories.
